revisions.description: Add hwAclAdvancedPktLenOp, hwAclAdvancedPktLenBegin and hwAclAdvancedPktLenEnd in hwAclAdvancedRuleTable.
Add hwAclAdvancedVni, hwAclAdvancedIgmpType, hwAclAdvancedTtlOp, hwAclAdvancedTtlExpire, hwAclAdvancedTtlExpireEnd in hwAclAdvancedRuleTable.

Change the range of hwAclNumGroupAclNum in hwAclNumGroupTable, hwAclBasicAclNum in hwAclBasicRuleTable, hwAclAdvancedAclNum in hwAclAdvancedRuleTable, hwAclIfAclNum in hwAclIfRuleTable, hwAclUserAclNum in hwAclUserRuleTable, hwAclIpv6BasicAclNum in hwAclIpv6BasicRuleTable, hwAclIpv6AdvancedAclNum in hwAclIpv6AdvancedRuleTable, hwAclEthernetFrameAclNum in hwAclEthernetFrameRuleTable, hwAclIpv6NumGroupAclNum ihwAclAdvancedSubitemn hwAclIpv6NumGroupTable, hwAclIpv6IfAclNum in hwAclIpv6IfRuleTable, hwAclMplsAclNum in hwAclMplsRuleTable.
Add hwAclIpv6BasicSrcMask in hwAclIpv6BasicRuleTable; Add hwAclIpv6AdvancedSrcMask, hwAclIpv6AdvancedDestMask in hwAclIpv6AdvancedRuleTable
Chang hwAclNumGroupAclName in hwAclIpv6NumGroupTable and hwAclIpv6NumGroupAclName in hwAclNumGroupTable value length

hwAcl.description: The HUAWEI-ACL-MIB contains objects to configure ACL module, including ACL group, rule and acl accelerate, and query the current ACL configuration and status. This MIB module objects indicate hwAclNumGroupTable, hwAclBasicRuleTable, hwAclAdvanceRuleTable, hwAclIfRuleTable, hwAclEthernetFrameRuleTable, hwAclIpv6BasicRuleTable, hwAclIpv6AdvanceRuleTable, hwAclIpv6IfRuleTable, hwAclCompileEnableFlag, hwAclCompileNumGroupTable, hwAclIpv6NumGroupTable and acl trap. To filter data packets, a series of rules need to be configured on the device. These rules are defined by ACL (Access Control List), which are a series of sequential rules consisting of rule permit or deny statements. The rules are described by source address, destination address and port number of data packets. ACL classifies data packets through these device interface applied rules, by which the device decides which packets can be received and which should be rejected.

hwAclNumGroupTable.name: hwAclNumGroupTable
hwAclNumGroupTable.description: The table of ACL group information including match order, step, description and so on

hwAclNumGroupEntry.name: hwAclNumGroupEntry
hwAclNumGroupEntry.description: An entry containing characters of an acl group

hwAclNumGroupAclNum.name: hwAclNumGroupAclNum
hwAclNumGroupAclNum.description: The index of acl group, identifying an ACL. The object specifies the range of an ACL number. The basic ACL is represented by the number in the range 2000 through 2999. The advanced ACL is represented by the number in the range 3000 through 3999. The interface-based ACL is represented by the number in the range 1000 to 1999. The User Defined ACL is represented by the number in the range 5000 through 5999. The User ACL is represented by the number in the range 6000 through 9999. The Mpls ACL is represented by the number in the range 10000 through 10999. The name ACL is represented by the number in the range 42768 through 76535.

hwAclNumGroupMatchOrder.name: hwAclNumGroupMatchOrder
hwAclNumGroupMatchOrder.description: The object indicates the match order of rules. 'config' means matching ACL rules in the configuration sequence, 'auto' means the ACL rules are matched following the 'Depth-first' principle.

hwAclNumGroupSubitemNum.name: hwAclNumGroupSubitemNum
hwAclNumGroupSubitemNum.description: The total number of the rules in the acl group.

hwAclNumGroupStep.name: hwAclNumGroupStep
hwAclNumGroupStep.description: The object indicates the step value of number acl. Step here refers to the difference between each ID. For instance, given the step is set to 5, the IDs are the multiples of 5 beginning with 5. The ACL IDs change along with the step. When the step is 5, the ACL IDs are 5, 10, and 15 and so on. However, when the step is set to 2, the IDs turn to 2, 4, and 6 and so on.

hwAclNumGroupDescription.name: hwAclNumGroupDescription
hwAclNumGroupDescription.description: The object indicates the description of this acl group. The object describes the usage of an ACL with a word or a sentence.

hwAclNumGroupCountClear.name: hwAclNumGroupCountClear
hwAclNumGroupCountClear.description: Reset the statistics of ACL group.

hwAclNumGroupAclName.name: hwAclNumGroupAclName
hwAclNumGroupAclName.description: The object indicates the name of an acl group, The first character must be start with a to z or A to Z, and the length cannot exceed 64 character.

hwAclBasicRuleTable.name: hwAclBasicRuleTable
hwAclBasicRuleTable.description: Configure the rule for basic acl group.

hwAclBasicRuleEntry.name: hwAclBasicRuleEntry
hwAclBasicRuleEntry.description: Each entry is a rule of basic acl.

hwAclBasicAclNum.name: hwAclBasicAclNum
hwAclBasicAclNum.description: The index of basic acl group, the index range is (1..99 | 2000..2999 | 42768..76535 ).

hwAclBasicSubitem.name: hwAclBasicSubitem
hwAclBasicSubitem.description: The objects specifies the number of an ACL rule. If the number specified has been assigned to an ACL rule, the new rule will overwrite the old one, which is equal to editing the old rule. If the number is not assigned, the system will define a rule with the number and insert it to the place corresponding to its number. If no number is specified, the system will define a rule, assign a number to it and add it into the ACL. It will be placed at the end of the ACL when configuration sequence is adopted; otherwise, it will be placed based on the 'Depth-first' principle. When ACL rules are following the 'Depth-first' principle, the number of an ACL rule must be given 0 ,but it will be assigned by step automatically;otherwise,this rule will not be created.

hwAclBasicAct.name: hwAclBasicAct
hwAclBasicAct.description: The object indicates the action of a basic acl rule. 'deny' means discarding the packets that meet the condition, 'permit' means permitting the packets that meet the condition.

hwAclBasicSrcIp.name: hwAclBasicSrcIp
hwAclBasicSrcIp.description: The object indicates the source IP-address of a basic acl rule.

hwAclBasicSrcWild.name: hwAclBasicSrcWild
hwAclBasicSrcWild.description: The object indicates the source IP-address wild of a basic acl rule.

hwAclBasicTimeRangeIndex.name: hwAclBasicTimeRangeIndex
hwAclBasicTimeRangeIndex.description: The object indicates the time range of a basic acl rule. When the current time is in time range, the rule is valid. Zero value declares that the acl rule has no time range. The invalid value is 0.

hwAclBasicFragments.name: hwAclBasicFragments
hwAclBasicFragments.description: The object indicates the type of the packet. 0: fragmentSubseq, indicating that the packet is a subsequent fragment 1: fragment, indicating that the packet is a fragment 2: nonFragment, indicating that the packet is not a fragment 3: nonSubseq, indicating that the packet is not a subsequent fragment 4: fragmentSpeFirst, indicating that the packet is the first fragment 255: none, invalid value This object cannot be modified once a rule is created.

hwAclBasicLog.name: hwAclBasicLog
hwAclBasicLog.description: The object indicates whether to log the matched packets. The log contents include sequence number of ACL rule, packets passed or discarded, upper layer protocol type over IP, source/destination address, source/destination port number, and number of packets.

hwAclBasicEnable.name: hwAclBasicEnable
hwAclBasicEnable.description: The object indicates whether the rule is valid or invalid.

hwAclBasicCount.name: hwAclBasicCount
hwAclBasicCount.description: The object indicates the statistics of matched packets by the rule.

hwAclBasicVrfName.name: hwAclBasicVrfName
hwAclBasicVrfName.description: The object indicates the VRF name of this rule. It specifies the VPN-instance to which the packet belongs.

hwAclBasicRowStatus.name: hwAclBasicRowStatus
hwAclBasicRowStatus.description: RowStatus, Now support three value:CreateAndGo,Active and Destroy.

hwAclBasicDescription.name: hwAclBasicDescription
hwAclBasicDescription.description: The object indicates the description of this basic rule. The object describes the usage of an ACL with a word or a sentence.
